Send me all your prayers, thoughts, and good vibes. Today is going to be a great day.

30 auditions in 30 seconds. Some favorites from 2022.

I love this job. And I’m proud of how much versatility you can see in this small glimpse of my work. How many costumes I have on hand just in case. How many dialects you can hear. How many different tones there are in the things I’ve auditioned for.

I don’t always get hired for the role, but I am always working.

March 2023. One second every day.
Universal Studios Hollywood’s world famous studio tour is hiring!
Support "Sketch", a short film about what art reveals and relationships hide. Follow our Seed & Spark campaign to help us unlock filmmaker perks! And if you're able, please contribute! Link in Bio!

21 hours. It took 21 hours to hit 100% of our crowdfunding goal for @sketchthefilm. I’m flabbergasted. We’re going to be putting up a stretch goal (as soon as I figure out how to do that on the platform), but our @seedandspark is continuing to accept contributions in the meantime.

Thank you to everyone who has pledged, liked, followed, and shared already. Reminder that if our campaign gets 250 followers, we earn filmmaker perks that will make this process easier for us, so please follow!

Let’s go make some art. @carolyn.kras @thespomancer @art_on_my_sleeve @michaelvegas

Happy Siblings’ Day!
@petersauer @spooky_balls

We launched our campaign two weeks ago today and have now hit 250 followers! It's a huge accomplishment. Thank you everyone for your interest and support. :)

Here's the message we received from Seed & Spark this morning:
 
"Congratulations! You’re eligible for Level I Rewards

You did it! You’re eligible for one of our Quarterly Perks as part of our #DiversityIsAlwaysOn initiative. Don’t worry, you don’t need to do anything. If your project is selected, someone from our team will reach out with additional information."

We are thrilled! The next level to aim for is 500 followers, which would earn us free festival submissions (and more)! We'd love for you to spread the word so that we can grow our network. We wrote some messages at the bottom of our main page that you can copy and paste to easily share on social media. :)
 
Sketch is now 133% funded. We are currently at $7750 and our stretch goal is $7820. We are so close to being able to hire an incredible production designer, DeAnne Millais, and rent our location for a second day so that she can get it looking perfect for filming.

Thank you again for all of your love. We are ecstatic and cannot wait to make this art.

Love,

The Sketch Team

On Sunday, we filmed a project that I’ve been dreaming into existence for years. A short film called Sketch.

I am so proud of what we accomplished on that day. And I can’t wait for it to be finished. I want you to see it.

How I did on my 2023 goals. It’s been a heck of a year. (Note: if I accomplished most of a goal, I counted it. Celebrating the wins.)

Yesterday I shared my goal progress in 2023. But some of the coolest things I did this year were things I hadn’t planned to do.

(Also, technically I’m seeing Something Corporate later tonight, but I put them on the list in advance.)

23 Auditions from 2023 in 23 seconds.

It’s incredible that I had so many auditions in a year where the industry was mostly on strike. Grateful for my team. (By the way, I booked my role on Quantum Leap and my role in the play Seared because of two of these self-tapes.)
